726001f-a.title: Queens: 209th Place - 111th Avenue
726001f-a.text:
209th Place, east side, looking south between One Hundred
Eleventh Ave. (foreground)and 111th Road, showing a rear view of
the J. Rhodes farmhouse. View No. 2 shows an easterly view from
Colfax Street. See other views for more data.
April 1925.
View 2: May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

726000f-c.title: Queens: 209th Place - 111th Avenue
726000f-c.text:
209th Flace, east side, between 111th Road and One Hundred
Eleventh Ave., as seen from Colfax Ave., in the foreground. This was
the J. Rhodes farmhouse from 1860 to 1873. Jos. Herte was the owner from
1891 to 1896. This set of four views shows the front of the house
facing 111th Road.
1922.
Views 1,2,3 \& 4.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
